1. On je velika *dika* svog sela. (He is a great *pride* of his village.)
2. Moj deda uvek nosi svoju *diku* - staru vojničku kapu. (My grandpa always wears his *trophy* - an old military cap.)
3. Njegova *dika* i ponos su njegova deca. (His *pride* and joy are his children.)
4. *Dik* si što si uspeo da položiš ispit! (You are *proud* that you passed the exam!)
5. Kada god se setim tog momenta, osetim veliku *diku*. (Whenever I remember that moment, I feel great *pride*.)
6. Ona se *dikila* svojim novim automobilom. (She was *showing off* with her new car.)
7. Ne bi trebalo da se *dikimo* svojim uspehom, već da radimo još napornije. (We shouldn't *boast* about our success, but work even harder.)
8. Izgleda da je njegova *dikovina* uzela maha i ne može da podnese kritiku. (It seems like his *arrogance* has gotten out of control and can't handle criticism.)